SHE IS.

14:16.617 --> 14:17.851
NO, SHE'S NOT.

14:17.851 --> 14:19.820
[ DOOR OPENS ]

14:19.820 --> 14:21.287
HI.

14:21.287 --> 14:22.723
HI.

14:22.723 --> 14:23.790
HEY.

14:23.790 --> 14:25.892
JEFFERY THINKS YOUR CRAZY.
WHOA, WAIT ‐‐

14:25.892 --> 14:27.761
WHAT?
I NEVER SAID "CRAZY."

14:27.761 --> 14:30.831
HE SAID YOU'VE BEEN IN THE
BATHROOM, LAUGHING FOR HOURS.

14:30.831 --> 14:32.465
THAT IS NOT TRUE.

14:32.465 --> 14:34.300
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

14:34.300 --> 14:35.301
AMANDA.

14:35.301 --> 14:36.837
WHAT ARE YOU
STILL DOING HERE?

14:36.837 --> 14:39.305
I'M ‐‐ LISTEN,
I'M ONLY CONCERNED.

14:39.305 --> 14:42.876
JEFFERY, NO ONE IS EVER GONNA
TELL ME WHAT TO DO AGAIN, OKAY?

14:42.876 --> 14:45.579
YOU'RE NOT MY PARENTS,
SO STOP ACTING LIKE IT.

14:45.579 --> 14:49.415
PEOPLE HAVE TO GO SOMETIMES.
THAT'S WHAT HUMAN BEINGS DO.

14:49.415 --> 14:52.252
THAT'S IT, AMANDA.

14:52.252 --> 14:54.988
STAND UP FOR YOURSELF.

14:57.090 --> 14:59.593
YOU SEE, JEFFERY.

14:59.593 --> 15:02.636
THAT'S WHAT PEOPLE DO.

15:02.636 --> 15:06.039
THEY COME, AND THEY GO.

15:06.039 --> 15:09.543
THEY LIVE, AND THEY DIE.

15:09.543 --> 15:11.645
DIE?

15:13.947 --> 15:16.316
ARE YOU OKAY?

15:18.652 --> 15:20.987
MY BROTHER IS DEAD.

15:26.359 --> 15:28.361
[ SIGHS ]

15:29.930 --> 15:32.132
I'M SORRY, CANDACE.

15:37.003 --> 15:38.805
OH, MAN.

15:39.973 --> 15:42.042
I DIDN'T EVEN GET A CHANCE
TO SAY GOODBYE,

15:42.042 --> 15:45.411
BUT THAT'S MY LIFE, RIGHT?

15:45.411 --> 15:47.514
[ SCOFFS ]

15:47.514 --> 15:48.982
ARE YOU GONNA BE OKAY?

15:48.982 --> 15:50.717
[ SNIFFLES ]

15:50.717 --> 15:52.853
DO I LOOK OKAY?

15:54.721 --> 15:56.890
PEOPLE DIE.

15:59.025 --> 16:02.268
YEAH, THIS ISN'T HEALTHY.

16:02.268 --> 16:04.370
IT'S OKAY TO LET IT GO.

16:06.673 --> 16:08.909
LET GO OF WHAT?

16:08.909 --> 16:14.014
WHATEVER EMOTION YOU HAVE
CONNECTED TO LOSING HIM.

16:16.817 --> 16:20.353
I'VE ONLY GOT ONE EMOTION,
JEFFERY.

16:22.022 --> 16:24.090
JUST ONE.

16:24.090 --> 16:26.560
AND WHAT'S THAT?

16:26.560 --> 16:28.428
RAGE.

16:30.697 --> 16:32.699
RAGE.

16:34.801 --> 16:37.170
FOR WHOEVER DID THIS.

16:39.873 --> 16:42.142
AND FOR WHOEVER
DIDN'T HELP HIM.

16:50.016 --> 16:53.019
[ Sighing ] OH, MAN.

16:54.921 --> 16:56.590
I HOPE
SHE'S GONNA BE OKAY.

16:56.590 --> 16:58.458
YEAH, ME, TOO.

17:37.638 --> 17:39.506
OH.

17:41.374 --> 17:43.376
OH, I CAN SMELL HIM.

17:44.811 --> 17:48.649
LORD JESUS,
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO HELP ME.

17:52.553 --> 17:55.656
BUT NONETHELESS, LORD...

17:58.024 --> 18:00.734
...YOUR WILL BE DONE.

18:01.802 --> 18:04.671
YOUR FAITH IS INSPIRING TO ME,
HANNA.

18:06.472 --> 18:10.176
YOU OKAY?
YOU WANT TO LAY DOWN?

18:12.546 --> 18:15.716
I WANT MY SON.

18:15.716 --> 18:17.618
I KNOW.

18:17.618 --> 18:19.786
I KNOW.

18:19.786 --> 18:21.722
I'M SORRY.

18:24.124 --> 18:25.892
[ SNIFFLES ]

18:25.892 --> 18:27.928
HE WAS SUCH A GOOD BOY.

18:30.597 --> 18:32.599
OH.

18:32.599 --> 18:34.735
[ SIGHS ]

18:36.036 --> 18:39.372
FROM THE TIME HE WAS BORN,

18:39.372 --> 18:42.308
HE WOULD WAKE ME UP
AND HUG ME.

18:42.308 --> 18:44.578
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:44.578 --> 18:45.812
MM.

18:48.048 --> 18:55.321
I REMEMBER BEING SO STRESSED OUT
WITH WORK,

18:55.321 --> 18:57.924
SO TIRED.

18:59.259 --> 19:01.301
MY BABY.

19:01.301 --> 19:03.403
MM, MY BABY.

19:05.506 --> 19:08.809
WHEN HE WAS 5,

19:08.809 --> 19:13.113
HE USED THE STOVE
AND BURNED HIS LITTLE ARM.

19:13.113 --> 19:17.518
AND I ‐‐ I WAS ABOUT TO FUSS
OR SCREAM AT HIM OR SOMETHING.

19:17.518 --> 19:21.354
[ Voice breaking ] AND HE ‐‐
AND HE CAME TO ME,

19:21.354 --> 19:23.890
AND HE SAID, "MAMA,

19:23.890 --> 19:26.993
I WAS TRYING TO
MAKE YOU SOME BREAKFAST

19:26.993 --> 19:29.996
SO YOU WOULDN'T HAVE TO DO IT
FOR ME."

19:32.365 --> 19:35.569
"WHEN I GET BIG,
I'M GONNA BE RICH.

19:35.569 --> 19:38.505
AND I'M GONNA
TAKE CARE OF YOU.

19:38.505 --> 19:42.843
AND YOU WON'T HAVE TO
WORK THIS HARD."

19:45.846 --> 19:49.382
EVERYDAY,
I SEE HIM DRIVING THAT TRUCK,

19:49.382 --> 19:51.417
TRYING TO HELP ME OUT.

19:53.754 --> 19:56.456
I FEEL SO BAD,

19:56.456 --> 19:58.859
JUST SO BAD

19:58.859 --> 20:02.603
THAT HE WAS CHAINED TO
TRYING TO MAKE MY LIFE BETTER.

20:04.137 --> 20:06.773
I WANTED BETTER FOR <i>HIM.</i>

20:08.441 --> 20:10.410
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

20:12.713 --> 20:14.080
OH.

20:17.951 --> 20:19.886
[ SIGHS ]

20:22.656 --> 20:24.791
MY BOSS.

20:24.791 --> 20:27.360
MY EX‐BOSS.

20:28.795 --> 20:31.264
YOU GONNA GET IT?
NO.

20:31.264 --> 20:33.567
I GUESS SHE'S HEARD.

20:33.567 --> 20:35.969
I GUESS SHE HEARD.

20:37.538 --> 20:39.673
I CAN'T TALK TO HER.

20:41.407 --> 20:43.610
I CAN'T.

20:45.378 --> 20:48.181
I KNOW WHO DID THIS.

20:48.181 --> 20:49.883
WHO, HANNA?

20:52.986 --> 20:57.824
HER SON, WYATT CRYER...

20:57.824 --> 21:01.201
JUDGE CRYER'S SON.

21:09.342 --> 21:11.477
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

21:11.477 --> 21:13.379
HANNA, IT IS ME.

21:13.379 --> 21:16.216
PLEASE, PLEASE CALL ME.

21:18.619 --> 21:20.754
I KNOW YOU'RE ANGRY.

21:20.754 --> 21:22.889
I KNOW YOU'RE UPSET.

21:22.889 --> 21:25.425
BUT IT IS IMPERATIVE
THAT I TALK TO YOU.

21:25.425 --> 21:28.194
I HAVE SOMETHING VERY IMPORTANT
TO TELL YOU.

21:29.229 --> 21:31.765
IF YOU DON'T CALL ME BACK,
I'M COMING TO YOUR HOUSE.

21:31.765 --> 21:33.433
DO YOU HEAR ME?

21:33.433 --> 21:35.869
[ SIGHS ] I'VE BEEN CALLING YOU
ALL MORNING.

21:35.869 --> 21:38.138
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
PLEASE CALL ME.

21:38.138 --> 21:39.673
GOODBYE.

21:39.673 --> 21:41.241
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]
COME IN.

21:41.241 --> 21:43.176
[ DOOR OPENS ]

21:44.310 --> 21:45.311
JEFFERY.

21:45.311 --> 21:46.312
HI.

21:46.312 --> 21:48.248
HI.

21:48.248 --> 21:49.916
HOW ARE YOU?

21:49.916 --> 21:51.284
I'M GOOD.

21:51.284 --> 21:53.019
GOOD.

21:53.019 --> 21:54.254
IS WYATT HOME?

21:54.254 --> 21:55.455
MM‐HMM.
HE'S IN HIS ROOM.

21:55.455 --> 21:57.190
I CAN SEE HIM?
MM‐HMM.

21:57.190 --> 21:58.491
OKAY.

22:00.527 --> 22:02.335
UH, YOU KNOW WHAT?

22:02.335 --> 22:04.237
MISS CRYER...
MM‐HMM.

22:04.237 --> 22:06.239
...CAN I TALK TO YOU
FOR A SECOND?

22:06.239 --> 22:07.240
WELL, YEAH.

22:07.240 --> 22:09.676
IT'S ‐‐ IT'S ABOUT AMANDA.

22:09.676 --> 22:11.978
WHAT ABOUT HER?

22:11.978 --> 22:14.515
I THINK SHE MAY BE
HAVING A BREAK.

22:14.515 --> 22:16.149
A BREAK?

22:16.149 --> 22:17.283
YES.

22:17.283 --> 22:19.152
WHAT KIND OF BREAK?

22:19.152 --> 22:20.320
DISSOCIATIVE.

22:20.320 --> 22:22.689
AND YOU WOULD KNOW THIS
HOW?

22:22.689 --> 22:24.625
WELL, I'VE BEEN
SPENDING TIME WITH HER.

22:24.625 --> 22:25.826
WHERE?

22:25.826 --> 22:28.428
AT THEIR APARTMENT.

22:28.428 --> 22:30.430
SHE AND NINE.

22:31.965 --> 22:33.433
NINE?

22:34.701 --> 22:37.337
THAT GIRL.

22:37.337 --> 22:39.339
CANDACE?

22:39.339 --> 22:41.341
ONE AND THE SAME.

22:41.341 --> 22:43.109
YEAH.
YEAH.

22:45.211 --> 22:46.813
WHAT IS AMANDA DOING?

22:46.813 --> 22:48.815
WELL,
SHE'S NOT SLEEPING.

22:48.815 --> 22:51.417
SHE'S ‐‐
SHE HAS ERRATIC BEHAVIORS,

22:51.417 --> 22:54.020
DISASSOCIATING, NIGHTMARES,

22:54.020 --> 22:56.156
LEAVING
AT ALL HOURS OF THE NIGHT.

22:56.156 --> 22:59.793
AND THEN, WHEN I ASK HER WHERE
SHE'S GOING, SHE NEVER SAYS.

22:59.793 --> 23:04.070
NIGHT SWEATS ‐‐ ALL THE SAME
THINGS AS BEFORE.

23:04.070 --> 23:06.139
BUT BEFORE, IT WAS...

23:10.577 --> 23:13.814
BEFORE, JEFFERY,
IT WAS AFTER A TRAUMA.

23:15.549 --> 23:17.751
HAS SHE SAID
IF ANYTHING'S HAPPENED?

23:17.751 --> 23:19.553
OTHER THAN SUING YOU?

23:21.454 --> 23:23.123
YOU KNOW ABOUT THAT?

23:23.123 --> 23:25.391
YES.

23:25.391 --> 23:27.460
IS SHE REALLY SERIOUSLY
ABOUT IT?

23:27.460 --> 23:30.764
WHERE SHE STANDS IN PSYCHOSIS,
ANYTHING'S POSSIBLE.

23:30.764 --> 23:34.568
OF COURSE IT IS, WITH
A PUPPET MASTER LIKE THAT GIRL.

23:34.568 --> 23:37.470
SHE'S NOT INVOLVED,
MISS CRYER.

23:37.470 --> 23:39.940
TELL THAT TO SOMEONE ELSE.

23:39.940 --> 23:42.308
LOOK, I DIDN'T TELL YOU THIS
TO BLAME CANDACE.

23:42.308 --> 23:43.577
IT'S REALLY ABOUT AMANDA.

23:43.577 --> 23:46.146
WELL,
WHAT DO YOU PROPOSE I DO?

23:46.146 --> 23:47.413
GET HER SOME HELP.

23:47.413 --> 23:49.315
SHE HAS TO WANT IT,
JEFFERY.

23:49.315 --> 23:51.184
WELL, MISS CRYER,
IN THIS CASE,

23:51.184 --> 23:53.453
I THINK YOU MAY WANT TO
FORCE IT ON HER.

23:53.453 --> 23:56.723
YOU THINK IT'S THAT BAD?

23:56.723 --> 24:00.734
SHE ASKED ME
WHERE SHE COULD GET A GUN.

24:00.734 --> 24:02.202
A GUN?

24:02.202 --> 24:03.436
YES.

24:05.338 --> 24:07.941
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]
WHAT ON EARTH FOR?

24:10.577 --> 24:11.912
WELL...

24:11.912 --> 24:14.080
TELL ME.

24:15.849 --> 24:16.950
SHE ‐‐

24:16.950 --> 24:18.585
IS SHE THINKING ABOUT
TAKING HER OWN LIFE?

24:18.585 --> 24:20.854
NO.
NO, IT'S NOT THAT.

24:20.854 --> 24:23.356
[ SIGHS ]

24:24.891 --> 24:27.160
WELL, THEN, WHAT DOES SHE
NEED A GUN FOR?

24:29.129 --> 24:32.933
SHE WANTED IT FOR YOU,
MR. CRYER, AND WYATT.

24:32.933 --> 24:34.768
US?

24:34.768 --> 24:37.203
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

24:37.203 --> 24:39.740
SHE WANTED TO KILL YOU.

24:44.711 --> 24:46.246
OH.

24:48.248 --> 24:50.183
[ SIGHS ]

24:52.418 --> 24:53.419
YEAH.

24:53.419 --> 24:54.788
THAT'S NEW.

24:54.788 --> 24:56.723
YEAH, BUT THEN,
IN THE NEXT BREATH,

24:56.723 --> 24:58.091
SHE SAYS
SHE WAS JUST KIDDING.

24:58.091 --> 24:59.359
SO I DON'T KNOW.

24:59.359 --> 25:01.602
I JUST THINK THE WHOLE THING
NEEDS TO BE TAKEN SERIOUSLY.

25:03.469 --> 25:05.238
YEAH.

25:05.238 --> 25:07.541
IT SHOULD.

25:11.311 --> 25:13.013
THANK YOU, JEFFERY.

25:13.013 --> 25:15.215
YES, MA'AM.

25:16.983 --> 25:19.520
I KNOW NINE
IS ALL OVER THIS.

25:19.520 --> 25:21.287
WHO IS NINE?

25:23.123 --> 25:25.626
NO ONE IMPORTANT.

25:28.161 --> 25:30.330
GO ON UP.

25:36.036 --> 25:37.504
WE SHALL SEE.

25:39.506 --> 25:41.174
WE SHALL SEE.

25:48.081 --> 25:49.683
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
COME IN.

25:51.451 --> 25:52.553
HEY.

25:52.553 --> 25:53.554
HI.

25:53.554 --> 25:55.455
HOW ARE YOU?

25:56.723 --> 25:57.958
GOOD.

25:57.958 --> 26:00.433
WHAT'S GOING ON?

26:03.970 --> 26:06.306
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

26:07.541 --> 26:10.310
CANDACE'S BROTHER DIED.

26:13.714 --> 26:15.782
OH, NO.

26:16.950 --> 26:18.251
HE DIED?

26:18.251 --> 26:20.353
MM‐HMM.

26:23.389 --> 26:25.592
BUT THAT'S NOT IT.

26:25.592 --> 26:26.893
WHAT?

26:26.893 --> 26:29.229
WHAT MORE, JEFFERY?

26:29.229 --> 26:32.032
MY MOM HAS THE CAR.

26:33.600 --> 26:35.001
WHAT?

26:35.001 --> 26:36.670
YES.

26:40.607 --> 26:42.008
WHY?

26:42.008 --> 26:44.878
SHE'S HOLDING IT
AGAINST ME.

26:44.878 --> 26:47.047
SHE'S USING IT HOSTAGE.

26:47.047 --> 26:48.515
I'M CONFUSED.

26:48.515 --> 26:50.684
WHAT ‐‐ I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

26:50.684 --> 26:54.054
SHE WANTS ME TO GO BACK
TO THE WAY I WAS,

26:54.054 --> 26:56.823
OR SHE SAID
SHE WILL TURN ME IN.

26:59.560 --> 27:02.102
JEFFERY,
TURN YOU IN FOR WHAT?

27:03.837 --> 27:05.305
HELPING YOU, WYATT.

27:05.305 --> 27:07.574
[ SCOFFS ]

27:07.574 --> 27:09.209
HELPING ME?

27:09.209 --> 27:11.177
YEAH.

27:12.245 --> 27:13.780
JEFFERY,
YOU DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

27:13.780 --> 27:15.716
I KNOW THAT.

27:20.587 --> 27:22.889
IF SHE TURNS YOU IN,
SHE'S TURNING ME IN, TOO.

27:24.090 --> 27:25.692
I KNOW.

27:30.296 --> 27:32.599
BUT WHAT DOES SHE WANT?

27:32.599 --> 27:34.000
I TOLD YOU.

27:34.000 --> 27:36.336
SHE WANTS ME TO GO BACK
TO THE WAY THAT I WAS.

27:36.336 --> 27:38.471
AND WHAT DOES THAT MEAN,
JEFFERY?

27:40.941 --> 27:42.743
[ SIGHS ]

27:45.245 --> 27:48.715
SHE WANTS ME
TO LIVE AT THE FACILITY,

27:48.715 --> 27:53.565
TO GO BACK TO THE LIFE WITH
THE PATIENTS AND THE CLIENTS,

27:55.656 --> 27:57.958
GET A GIRLFRIEND,

27:57.958 --> 28:00.293
PRETEND TO BE SOMETHING
I'M NOT.

28:00.293 --> 28:02.736
PRETEND TO BE STRAIGHT,

28:02.736 --> 28:04.871
LIVE IN THE CLOSET.

28:04.871 --> 28:08.008
JEFFERY, SHE'S TALKING ABOUT
SENDING YOU TO PRISON.

28:09.242 --> 28:14.548
WYATT, I HAVE BEEN IN PRISON
ALL MY LIFE.

28:14.548 --> 28:17.083
AND NOW I COME OUT.

28:17.083 --> 28:21.855
[ SIGHS ] AND I GOT TO TELL YOU,
THIS WEEK HAS BEEN SO FREEING.

28:23.323 --> 28:25.125
I FEEL GOOD.

28:26.660 --> 28:29.830
AND I DON'T WANT TO GO BACK
TO THAT.

28:29.830 --> 28:32.733
NO.
SHE CAN'T ASK ME TO DO THAT.

28:34.535 --> 28:36.369
[ SIGHS ]

28:36.369 --> 28:38.004
MM.

28:38.004 --> 28:41.675
JEFFERY,
THIS IS OUR FREEDOM.

28:41.675 --> 28:43.577
THIS IS YOUR FREEDOM.

28:43.577 --> 28:46.980
EITHER WAY, I'M NOT FREE.

28:49.750 --> 28:51.685
[ SIGHS ]

28:56.857 --> 28:58.825
SO, WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

29:02.168 --> 29:04.070
I DON'T KNOW.

29:05.438 --> 29:08.174
YOU REALLY THINK SHE'S GONNA
TURN US IN IF YOU DON'T DO IT?

29:08.174 --> 29:10.677
YOU KNOW MY MOTHER.

29:10.677 --> 29:12.646
[ SIGHS ]

29:17.183 --> 29:19.285
THEN I SHOULD TELL MY DAD
THAT SHE HAS THE CAR.

29:19.285 --> 29:21.021
SHE WON'T CARE.

29:21.021 --> 29:22.022
THEN TELL YOUR DAD.

29:22.022 --> 29:24.057
SHE WON'T GIVE UP, MAN.

29:24.057 --> 29:27.360
SHE HAS ME
RIGHT WHERE SHE WANTS ME.

29:29.095 --> 29:31.164
THIS IS THAT IMPORTANT
TO HER?

29:32.398 --> 29:35.702
SHE DOESN'T WANT ME
TO BE WHO I AM.

29:35.702 --> 29:38.505
IT IS THAT IMPORTANT
TO HER.

29:41.474 --> 29:42.475
[ SIGHS ]

29:42.475 --> 29:44.745
SO, WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

29:46.379 --> 29:48.649
WHAT I HAVE TO.

29:48.649 --> 29:51.451
WHAT'S THAT?

29:53.186 --> 29:55.121
LIVE MY LIFE.
I'M NOT GOING BACK.

29:55.121 --> 29:56.823
JEFFERY.

29:56.823 --> 29:59.292
THIS IS ME TOO, MAN.

29:59.292 --> 30:01.401
I KNOW.

30:01.401 --> 30:03.970
YOU CAN'T DO THAT.

30:10.243 --> 30:12.378
TAKE YOUR CLOTHES OFF.

30:15.782 --> 30:17.017
WHAT?

30:17.017 --> 30:19.520
TAKE YOUR CLOTHES OFF.

30:19.520 --> 30:21.555
JEFFERY.

30:21.555 --> 30:24.257
YOU KNOW I WANT YOU.

30:25.592 --> 30:27.127
I'M NOT DOING THAT.

30:27.127 --> 30:28.929
[ SLAPS KNEE ]

30:28.929 --> 30:30.531
OKAY.

30:30.531 --> 30:32.298
OKAY.

30:32.298 --> 30:35.101
THEN I GUESS
YOU'VE MADE MY DECISION FOR ME.

30:36.336 --> 30:38.271
JEFFERY,
YOU CAN'T DO THAT TO ME.

30:38.271 --> 30:40.106
OH?

30:41.274 --> 30:44.678
OKAY. WELL, MAYBE
THAT WAS A LITTLE TOO MUCH.

30:46.780 --> 30:48.582
WE'LL START WITH A KISS.

30:50.984 --> 30:53.286
KISS ME.

30:55.488 --> 30:56.489
JEFFERY.

30:56.489 --> 30:58.592
KISS ME.

31:01.568 --> 31:03.469
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

31:13.046 --> 31:15.616
SEE HOW AWFUL THIS IS...

31:20.486 --> 31:22.556
...TO FOOL SOMEONE...

31:24.925 --> 31:27.227
...TO MAKE THEM
FEEL WORTHLESS...

31:29.696 --> 31:32.766
...TO USE THEM
FOR YOUR OWN SAKE?

31:35.135 --> 31:38.672
IF I WAS RUTHLESS LIKE CANDACE
OR MY MOTHER,

31:38.672 --> 31:42.408
YOU WOULD BE DOING
ANYTHING I ASKED YOU TO DO.

31:43.710 --> 31:45.746
BUT I'M NOT.

31:48.448 --> 31:50.416
YOU HURT ME, WYATT.

31:53.153 --> 31:56.022
BUT I STILL LOVE YOU,

31:56.022 --> 31:58.859
AND I'M STILL YOUR FRIEND.

32:02.503 --> 32:03.504
JEFFERY.

32:03.504 --> 32:05.238
LISTEN, I'M SORRY.

32:05.238 --> 32:07.508
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

32:07.508 --> 32:09.510
NOW WE'RE EVEN.

32:09.510 --> 32:11.978
[ SIGHS ]

32:14.748 --> 32:18.184
OKAY. SO...

32:18.184 --> 32:19.886
SO,
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

32:19.886 --> 32:22.022
I'M GONNA DO
WHAT I HAVE TO.

32:24.490 --> 32:27.360
I HAVE TO PROTECT
YOU AND ME.

32:29.830 --> 32:33.233
I'M SORRY.

32:33.233 --> 32:35.736
BUT THANK YOU.

32:53.520 --> 32:54.655
[ LOCK CLICKS ]

32:54.655 --> 32:56.389
WHO ARE YOU?

32:56.389 --> 32:58.258
VERONICA.

32:58.258 --> 33:00.126
DO I KNOW YOU?

33:00.126 --> 33:02.603
NO, YOU DON'T.

33:02.603 --> 33:05.405
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

33:05.405 --> 33:10.376
DO YOU KNOW A YOUNG LADY
BY THE NAME OF CANDACE YOUNG?

33:11.878 --> 33:13.046
WHY?

33:13.046 --> 33:14.548
BECAUSE I'D LIKE TO KNOW.

33:14.548 --> 33:17.217
NO, NO, NO, NO.
WHY YOU WANT TO KNOW?

33:17.217 --> 33:19.620
OH, YOU'RE ONE OF THEM.

33:21.221 --> 33:22.723
ONE OF WHAT?

33:22.723 --> 33:27.961
"NO SNITCH" OR WHATEVER THAT
GHETTO CRAP IS YOU GUYS SAY.

33:27.961 --> 33:30.396
WHAT DO YOU WANT, LADY?

33:30.396 --> 33:33.333
DO YOU WANT TO BE IN HERE
FOR THE REST OF YOUR LIFE?

33:33.333 --> 33:36.603
WHAT CAN YOU DO ABOUT IT?

33:36.603 --> 33:39.005
MAYBE I CAN HELP YOU
GET OUT.

33:39.005 --> 33:41.474
HOW?

33:41.474 --> 33:45.145
BY YOU ANSWERING MY QUESTION.
SO YOU KNOW CANDACE YOUNG?

33:45.145 --> 33:46.479
SUPPOSE I DO.

33:46.479 --> 33:49.249
IS SHE
THE MOTHER OF YOUR CHILD?

33:51.117 --> 33:52.285
MAYBE.

33:52.285 --> 33:54.655
IS SHE, OR IS SHE NOT?

33:58.058 --> 34:00.026
HOW YOU GONNA
GET ME OUT OF HERE?

34:00.026 --> 34:02.102
I AM A VERY POWERFUL WOMAN,

34:02.102 --> 34:04.505
AND I CAN MAKE THINGS HAPPEN
VERY QUICKLY.

34:04.505 --> 34:06.272
NOW, IS SHE?

34:06.272 --> 34:08.274
MAYBE.

34:08.274 --> 34:10.644
WHEN IS THE LAST TIME
YOU SPOKE WITH HER?

34:10.644 --> 34:13.079
YOU GOT TO TELL ME
SOMETHING.

34:14.147 --> 34:17.217
SHE HAS MADE
SOME VERY POWERFUL ENEMIES,

34:17.217 --> 34:20.153
AND THEY WOULD LIKE
TO SEE YOU GET OUT

34:20.153 --> 34:24.858
AND SPEND SOME TIME WITH HER,
PUTTING HER IN LINE,

34:24.858 --> 34:28.995
LIKE YOU SEEM TO HAVE DONE
SO DELICATELY IN THE PAST.

34:28.995 --> 34:29.996
SHE FELL.

34:29.996 --> 34:32.833
OH, SO YOU DO
KNOW CANDACE YOUNG.

34:32.833 --> 34:35.969
AND SHE MUST HAVE FALLEN
FROM A SKYSCRAPER.

34:35.969 --> 34:38.805
NOW, WHEN'S THE LAST TIME
YOU SPOKE WITH HER?

34:38.805 --> 34:40.273
[ SIGHS ]

34:40.273 --> 34:42.142
TWO YEAR AGO.

34:42.142 --> 34:44.110
WHY SO LONG?

34:44.110 --> 34:47.914
LOOK, I'M NOT GIVING HER UP
ON ANYTHING,

34:47.914 --> 34:52.352
SO IF YOU WANT ME TO SNITCH,
IT AIN'T HAPPENING.

34:52.352 --> 34:55.789
[ CHUCKLES ] IT'S FUNNY THAT
YOU WOULD BE SO LOYAL TO HER

34:55.789 --> 35:00.093
WHEN SHE DROPPED DIME ON YOU,
GAVE YOU UP.

35:00.093 --> 35:02.669
SHE WOULDN'T DO THAT.

35:02.669 --> 35:05.972
HOW DO YOU THINK
THEY KNEW SO MUCH ABOUT YOU,

35:05.972 --> 35:09.876
THINGS
THAT YOU ONLY TOLD HER?

35:11.077 --> 35:12.913
COME ON, QUINCY.
YOU'RE NOT THAT SLOW.

35:14.347 --> 35:17.350
I CAN'T LET MYSELF THINK
SHE'D DO THAT TO ME.

35:17.350 --> 35:20.386
DON'T LET YOURSELF THINK IT.
KNOW IT.

35:22.322 --> 35:24.825
HERE.
HERE'S THE FILE.

35:34.568 --> 35:36.236
SHE ‐‐

35:36.236 --> 35:38.071
SHE LOVES ME.

35:38.071 --> 35:40.874
SHE LOATHED YOU.
SHE HATED YOU.

35:40.874 --> 35:44.210
SHE'S LIVING IT UP,
AND YOU'RE IN HERE.

35:44.210 --> 35:46.680
YOU DON'T SEEM TO
WANT TO GET OUT.

35:47.948 --> 35:49.583
WHAT DO I HAVE TO DO?

35:49.583 --> 35:51.251
TO GET OUT?

35:52.619 --> 35:54.054
YES.

35:54.054 --> 35:56.189
HANDLE YOUR BUSINESS.

35:56.189 --> 35:58.559
ISN'T THAT
WHAT YOU GUYS SAY?

35:58.559 --> 36:01.434
I'LL BE IN TOUCH WITH YOU.

36:06.740 --> 36:08.408
YOU...

36:09.843 --> 36:12.779
...ARE ABOUT TO RECEIVE
A PAROLE HEARING.

36:12.779 --> 36:14.781
[ CHUCKLES ]

36:26.026 --> 36:27.928
THANK YOU.
YOU'RE VERY WELCOME.

36:27.928 --> 36:29.663
IT'S THE LEAST
WE COULD DO.

36:29.663 --> 36:31.231
I HAD SOMEONE BRING
YOUR CAR AROUND.

36:31.231 --> 36:32.633
OH.
THANK YOU.

36:32.633 --> 36:34.835
WE'RE ON ALL
THE NATIONAL NETWORKS.

36:34.835 --> 36:38.471
HIS PICTURE WENT EVERYWHERE.
WE'RE GONNA CATCH THIS GUY.

36:38.471 --> 36:39.740
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

36:39.740 --> 36:41.207
SURE.

36:41.207 --> 36:43.844
DO YOU HAVE TIME
TO TALK TO CNN?

36:43.844 --> 36:45.712
UH...

36:45.712 --> 36:48.214
SORRY, REVEREND.
WE REALLY DO HAVE TO GO.

36:48.214 --> 36:49.750
WELL,
IT'LL ONLY TAKE A SECOND.

36:49.750 --> 36:52.018
NO. WE HAVE TIME.

36:52.018 --> 36:54.821
THIS IS FOR THE VICTIMS
IN THIS CASE, REVEREND.

36:54.821 --> 36:58.391
I'M SORRY. IT'S NOT A GOOD TIME
FOR A POLITICAL SPEECH.

36:58.391 --> 37:00.761
WELL, I RESPECT THAT.

37:00.761 --> 37:02.902
WHAT YOU HAVE DONE
WILL GO A LONG WAY.

37:02.902 --> 37:04.738
THANK YOU.
YOU'RE VERY WELCOME.

37:04.738 --> 37:06.940
LET'S GO ON.
LET'S GET IN.

37:06.940 --> 37:08.942
WHAT THE HELL WAS THAT?

37:08.942 --> 37:09.943
WHAT?

37:09.943 --> 37:12.345
WE HAD AN IN.
THAT WAS CNN.

37:12.345 --> 37:15.649
WELL, WE HAD TO TAKE A PASS.
WE'RE TIRED.

37:15.649 --> 37:18.217
CUT THE CRAP.
WHAT IS GOING ON HERE?

37:18.217 --> 37:20.053
I'LL TELL YOU AT THE OFFICE.

37:20.053 --> 37:21.588
[ CELLPHONE RINGS, BEEPS ]

37:21.588 --> 37:23.757
YOU BETTER. YOU BETTER
HAVE SOME ANSWERS FOR ME.

37:23.757 --> 37:25.792
I WILL, AT THE OFFICE.

37:25.792 --> 37:27.293
YEAH.

37:28.662 --> 37:30.531
REALLY?

37:32.098 --> 37:33.600
OKAY.

37:33.600 --> 37:34.601
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

37:34.601 --> 37:35.602
WHAT WAS THAT?

37:35.602 --> 37:36.603
HANNA.

37:36.603 --> 37:37.971
WHAT ABOUT HER?

37:37.971 --> 37:40.641
SHE JUST MADE
THE FIRST MOVE.

37:41.942 --> 37:43.276
MM‐HMM.

37:43.276 --> 37:44.945
COME ON.

37:50.350 --> 37:53.053
COME ON.
I MADE US LUNCH.

37:59.560 --> 38:01.501
[ SIGHS ]

38:05.038 --> 38:07.373
I'M SO SORRY, CANDACE.

38:07.373 --> 38:09.375
IT'S FINE.

38:09.375 --> 38:11.512
PEOPLE DIE.

38:11.512 --> 38:14.815
HOW CAN YOU BE SO STRONG?

38:17.017 --> 38:18.885
IT'S MY LIFE.

38:18.885 --> 38:20.554
PEOPLE DIE.

38:20.554 --> 38:22.122
MEN DIE.

38:22.122 --> 38:24.024
BABIES DIE.

38:24.024 --> 38:26.426
PEOPLE JUST DIE.

38:27.528 --> 38:29.462
BABIES?

38:34.267 --> 38:36.603
JEFFERY,
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

38:36.603 --> 38:40.206
I'M OFF TO CAMPAIGN HEADQUARTERS
FOR MY DAD.

38:41.708 --> 38:43.744
AND YOU NEED A SUITCASE
FOR THAT?

38:43.744 --> 38:46.079
WELL, THEN I'M MOVING
BACK INTO MY PLACE.

38:46.079 --> 38:49.215
SO THANK YOU
FOR ALL OF YOUR HOSPITALITY.

38:54.454 --> 38:55.756
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

38:55.756 --> 38:58.191
WHEREVER HE'S GOING,
JUST LET HIM GO.

38:58.191 --> 39:01.401
I'M MOVING
BACK INTO MY APARTMENT.

39:01.401 --> 39:03.169
OH,
SO YOUR MOM CAME AROUND.

39:03.169 --> 39:05.438
YES.

39:05.438 --> 39:07.708
NO, SHE DIDN'T.

39:10.844 --> 39:12.378
HOW DID SHE DO IT?

39:14.180 --> 39:17.117
IS IT MONEY?

39:17.117 --> 39:18.284
NO.

39:18.284 --> 39:20.320
THAT'S NOT IT.

39:21.655 --> 39:23.356
WHAT DID SHE DO TO YOU?

39:25.058 --> 39:26.960
I JUST ‐‐ I HAVE TO.

39:26.960 --> 39:29.395
WHAT DID SHE DO TO YOU,
JEFFERY?

39:29.395 --> 39:32.566
I'M SORRY.

39:34.701 --> 39:35.736
FINE.

39:35.736 --> 39:37.971
GO ON TO YOUR LITTLE
CAMPAIGN HEADQUARTERS.

39:37.971 --> 39:41.041
NEED TO TEACH YOU TWO BITCHES
HOW TO BE RUTHLESS.

39:41.041 --> 39:42.909
I'M NOT A BITCH.

39:42.909 --> 39:45.411
THAT'S THE PROBLEM.

39:45.411 --> 39:47.080
GO ON.

39:47.080 --> 39:48.381
GO.

39:50.083 --> 39:52.553
WELL, THANKS FOR EVERYTHING.

39:52.553 --> 39:54.254
[ SCOFFS ]

39:54.254 --> 39:56.122
YEAH, WHATEVER.

40:05.005 --> 40:06.973
[ DOOR OPENS ]

40:06.973 --> 40:09.075
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

40:12.212 --> 40:15.415
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN TO HIM?

40:15.415 --> 40:16.416
WYATT CRYER?

40:16.416 --> 40:18.118
YEAH.

40:18.118 --> 40:21.522
I'M NOT SURE, BUT HE WILL
DEFINITELY GO TO JAIL.

40:27.427 --> 40:29.596
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

40:38.672 --> 40:40.741
YES?
WE'RE LOOKING FOR HANNA YOUNG.

40:40.741 --> 40:42.442
WHAT DO YOU WANT WITH HER?

40:42.442 --> 40:43.844
WE HAVE A WARRANT
FOR HER ARREST, SIR.

40:43.844 --> 40:45.779
FOR WHAT?

40:45.779 --> 40:47.814
LET ME SEE THAT.

40:47.814 --> 40:50.751
IS SHE HERE?

40:50.751 --> 40:52.252
HANNA YOUNG?

40:52.252 --> 40:53.654
Hanna: YES.

40:53.654 --> 40:55.088
HANNA YOUNG,
YOU'RE UNDER ARREST.

40:55.088 --> 40:57.023
FOR WHAT?

40:57.023 --> 40:59.492
SHE DOESN'T NEED THE CUFFS.

40:59.492 --> 41:01.735
SORRY, SIR.
SHE HAS TO COME WITH US.

41:01.735 --> 41:03.670
BYRON.
PLEASE.

41:03.670 --> 41:05.572
I'M THERE, HANNA.

41:05.572 --> 41:06.873
I'M THERE.

41:06.873 --> 41:09.743
OH.

41:09.743 --> 41:12.445
[ HANDCUFFS CLICK ]

41:21.421 --> 41:23.456
[ CAR DOOR OPENS ]

41:25.325 --> 41:27.528
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

41:43.009 --> 41:45.378
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

41:51.084 --> 41:53.453
<i>NEXT WEEK ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS"...</i>

41:53.453 --> 41:55.989
YOU HAVE JUST OFFICIALLY
BECOME MY ENEMY.

41:55.989 --> 41:57.891
YOU CAN'T AFFORD ME
AS AN ENEMY.

41:57.891 --> 41:59.159
WHAT IS GOING ON?

41:59.159 --> 42:01.635
HOW DO YOU WANT TO
HANDLE THE PROBLEM NOW?
